---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
const updated = '2026-07-02';
---

<BaseLayout title="Cookie Policy" description="How VisaLang uses analytics, preference cookies, and third-party embeds while keeping language-exam route guidance privacy-conscious." noindex={true}>
  <main class="page-shell">
    <article class="guide-article narrow-page">
        <p class="eyebrow">Legal</p>
        <h1>Cookie Policy</h1>
        <p class="guide-summary">Last updated: {updated}</p>

        <h2>What are cookies</h2>
        <p>Cookies are small text files stored in your browser. VisaLang uses them sparingly.</p>

        <h2>Cookies we use</h2>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Analytics cookies:</strong> Plausible Analytics uses a privacy-friendly cookie to count visits. No cross-site tracking.</li>
          <li><strong>Preference cookies:</strong> if you switch the site language, your choice may be remembered locally.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Cookies we do not use</h2>
        <p>We do not currently use advertising cookies, retargeting cookies, or third-party social-media tracking cookies. If we add display advertising in the future, we will update this policy and provide a consent mechanism where required.</p>

        <h2>Managing cookies</h2>
        <p>You can clear or block cookies in your browser settings. Disabling cookies may affect some site features.</p>

        <h2>Third-party embeds</h2>
        <p>If we embed official videos or resources from external providers, those providers may set their own cookies.</p>

        <p class="compliance-line">See also our <a href="/privacy-policy/">Privacy Policy</a>.</p>
        <p class="last-updated">Last updated: {updated}</p>
    </article>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>
